SMART FLOOR CLEANER ROBOT – COMPONENTS AND THEIR PURPOSE

1. Arduino Uno
Arduino Uno acts as the main controller or brain of the system. It receives data from the ultrasonic sensor, processes the information, 
and controls the movement of the robot through the motor driver module.
- Easy to program and interface
- Supports multiple input and output connections
- Suitable for embedded and robotics applications
- Reads obstacle distance from sensor
- Controls robot movement
- Sends control signals to motor driver


2. HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor

The ultrasonic sensor is used for obstacle detection. It continuously measures the distance between the robot and 
nearby objects.

- Accurate distance measurement
- Low cost and easy interfacing
- Works without physical contact
- Detects obstacles in front of the robot
- Sends distance information to Arduino
- Helps the robot avoid collisions


3. L298N Motor Driver Module
The motor driver module controls the speed and direction of the DC motors.

- Arduino cannot provide enough current to run motors directly
- Motor driver supplies required current and voltage
- Receives control signals from Arduino
- Drives left and right motors
- Controls forward, backward, and turning movements


4. DC Geared Motors
DC motors are responsible for the movement of the robot.
- Provides rotational motion
- Geared motors provide better torque and control
- Moves the robot forward and backward
- Enables left and right turning
- Supports robot navigation


5. Cleaning Fan / Brush Motor
The cleaning motor rotates the cleaning brush or fan to collect dust from the floor.

- Performs the actual cleaning operation
- Rotates continuously during robot movement
- Collects dust and small particles
- Helps in floor cleaning automation


6. Rechargeable Battery

Battery provides electrical power to all components in the system.

- Makes the robot portable
- Allows operation without direct power connection
- Powers Arduino, motors, and sensors
- Supplies continuous energy during movement


7. Robot Chassis

The chassis acts as the physical body of the robot.

- Holds all components together
- Provides mechanical support
- Supports motors, battery, and controller
- Maintains robot structure and stability

8. Wheels

Wheels help the robot move smoothly on the floor.

- Converts motor rotation into movement
- Supports directional motion
- Enables movement across surfaces
- Helps in navigation


9. Connecting Wires

Connecting wires establish electrical connections between all components.
- Transfers signals and power
- Ensures communication between modules
- Connects Arduino, sensor, motor driver, and battery


10. Power Switch

The switch is used to turn the robot ON or OFF.

- Provides easy control of power supply
- Starts and stops system operation


11. Breadboard / PCB

Used for arranging and connecting electronic components.

- Simplifies circuit assembly
- Supports prototyping
- Holds connections securely
- Organizes the circuit layout


12. LED Indicators

LEDs indicate the operational status of the system.

- Provides visual indication
- Indicates power ON condition
- Helps during testing and debugging
